command.narcissus_farewell.uuid_detail: Get the UUID of the player
command.narcissus_farewell.card_detail:
Get or modify the number of Teleport Card for a player. No parameters are needed to check your own card count.
Parameters:
 1. get <player>
 2. add <player> <num>
 3. set <player> <num>
command.narcissus_farewell.share_detail:
Share the stage, the personal home, and the current coordinate of player. Symbol “->” indicates a personal home, and “>>” indicates a stage (public waypoint). If the symbol is empty or custom, the player's current coordinates will be shared by default.
Parameters:
 1. [<name>]
 2. [<stage symbol>] [<player>]
 3. [<home symbol>] [<player>]
command.narcissus_farewell.feed_detail:
Try the narcissus tea yourself or ask others to try it, the effect is similar to /kill.
Parameters:
 [<player>]

Teleport to a specified coordinate or player.
Parameters:

 2. <coordinates> [<safe teleport>] [<dimension>]
command.narcissus_farewell.tp_structure_:
Teleport to a specified structure or biome (default is safe).

 2. <biome> [<search distance>] [<dimension>] [<safe teleport>]

command.narcissus_farewell.tp_home_detai:
Teleport to a pre-set personal waypoint. Each dimension can have a default waypoint.
If no waypoint name is specified:
- If there is only one personal waypoint, it will be used.
- If multiple personal waypoint exist but only one default, the default will be used.
- If multiple default personal waypoints exist, the one in the current dimension will be used.
Parameters:
 1. [<personal waypoint name>] [<safe teleport>] [<dimension>]
2. [<safe teleport>] [<dimension>]
command.narcissus_farewell.set_home_deta:
Add the player's current coordinates to the personal waypoint list. If no name is specified, the default name 'home' will be used.
Parameters:
 [<waypoint name>] [<set as default>]
command.narcissus_farewell.del_home_deta:
Delete a previously set personal waypoint. The current dimension ID can be queried with a command.
Parameters:
 <waypoint name> <dimension>
command.narcissus_farewell.get_home_deta: Get details of the personal waypoint list, including coordinates and dimension information.
command.narcissus_farewell.tp_stage_deta:
Teleport to a pre-set stage (public waypoint). If no name is specified, the nearest waypoint will be used.
Parameters:

command.narcissus_farewell.set_stage_det:
Add the current or specified coordinates to a stage (public waypoint).
Parameters:

command.narcissus_farewell.del_stage_det:
Delete a previously set stage (public waypoint). The current dimension ID can be queried with a command.
Parameters:
 <waypoint name>] [<dimension>
command.narcissus_farewell.get_stage_det: Get details of the stage (public waypoint) list, including coordinates and dimension information.
